The paper deals with the application of Compressive Sensing (CS) to observability of linear systems, which falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of randomized measurement operators and the analysis of Concentration of Measure (CoM) inequalities are also relevant to the Statistical Learning (cs.SI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves numerical analysis and simulations, which are relevant to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of state transition matrices, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
